Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and
preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @Long Green Pepper{1} into strips. Halve, peel, and
thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}.

Toss green pepper on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tbsp},
half the @Fry Seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack
until golden brown and tender, ~{20-22%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion;
season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until browned and softened,
~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @Ground Beef{10%oz}, remaining @Fry Seasoning{1/2%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.
Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Slice @Demi-Baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through.
Toast, cut sides up, in oven until lightly golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Once beef is done, stir in @Beef Stock Concentrate{1}, @Dijon Mustard{2%tsp},
and @water{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Top with @Mexican Cheese Blend{1/2%cup};
cover pan until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Fill baguettes with beef filling and roasted green pepper. Top with as much
@Hot Sauce{1%tsp} as you like.

Divide sandwiches and @Blue Corn Tortilla Chips{1.5%oz} between plates. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.